'''''Iris spuria''''' is a species of the genus [[Iris (plant)|Iris]], part of a subgenus series known as ''[[Limniris]]''. The slender and elogated leaves surround a purple flower. It is a beardless form, sometimes known as the '''blue iris'''.

The species is widely cultivated and hybridized for use in the garden. It is found in Europe, Asia and Africa.
It was first described in 1753 by [[Linnaeus]], who described it in the ''[[Species Plantarum]]'' as being  German.
